reports.missionName: The first rule of space travel kids is always check out distress beacons. Nine out of ten times it's a ship full of dead aliens and a bunch of free shit! One out of ten times it's a deadly trap, but... I'm ready to roll those dice!
Get off the high road Summer. We all got pink eye because you wouldn't stop texting on the toilet.
So what if the most meaningful day in your life was a simulation operating at minimum complexity.
